	<section>
	<h3 class="div1head">Client-Side Web Development Tools</h3>
	<details>
	<summary>Bootstrap</summary>
		<ul>
			<li>Bootstrap is an open source toolkit for developing with HTML, CSS, and JS. Quickly prototype your ideas or build your entire app with our Sass variables and mixins, responsive grid system, extensive prebuilt components, and powerful plugins built on jQuery.</li>
			<li><a href="www.bootstrap.com">Link to tool</a></li>
		</ul>
	</details>
	<details>
	<summary>NPM or "Node Package Manager</summary>
		<ul>
			<li>NPM is a package manager for JavaScript that helps discover packages of reusable code and assemble them in new ways that makes them more powerful.</li>
			<li><a href="https://www.npmjs.com/">Link to tool</a></li>
		</ul>
	</details>
	<details>
	<summary>w3Schools</summary>
		<ul>
			<li>W3Schools is optimized for learning, testing, and training. Examples might be simplified to improve reading and basic understanding.</li>
			<li><a href="https://www.typescriptlang.org/index.html">Link to tool</a></li>
		</ul>
